	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=60915"><span id="Scholar">The One and Only Opee</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">63 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I think you have discovered the true intent of the Casino on the game.<br/><br/>If you have read some of the threads from the Devs of these types of on line games, then you know that there is a lot of effort put into trying to balance the economies. There was an extensive thread on this issue on the dev boards of SWG. One of the hallmarks (and necessary components) is what is known as a &quot;sink.&quot; A sink, quite briefly, is something that removes currency (Plat) from the game. Tradeskills are a big sink in EQ as well as mounts, since they take plat out of circulation. Without sinks, there is an endless supply of currency, and price inflation is inevitable.<br/>I think the Casino was an attempt to create another large plat sink for the EQ economy, but just a ranger's hunch. I imagine that we will see something akin to it in an upcoming patch.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Opee, Rider of the Purple Sage.<br/></td></tr>
